Based on the meeting discussion, here are the details for crafting the maritime safety narrative for Ken's board assessment:

Purpose and Context:
Ken has a board assessment in April with a new rubric format
Ken needs documentation from senior executives to create his narrative and presentation
Partnerships is one of the key areas Ken will be questioned on
The deadline is flexible (review isn't until April), but Ken wants materials in the next few weeks to prepare

Key Themes for Maritime Safety Narrative:
Eric identified three major themes to highlight:
Hire-Train-Deploy Model through CTR - A new academic model that differs from traditional approaches, exemplified by the CTR welding training initiative
Custom Curriculum through Continuing Education - This concept extends beyond CTR to LiveView Technology and 3-4 other 2025-2026 initiatives
Pathways from Skilled Trades - Opening up new educational pathways that originated from maritime safety work

Process:
Eric and Caroline will work together to craft the maritime safety narrative
Send completed materials to Caroline, who will consolidate everything into a shared folder for Ken
Caroline will upload all documentation to Ken's board assessment folder

The narrative should demonstrate how maritime safety partnerships have evolved into broader university initiatives and innovative educational models.
